<paragraph blockId="54.[151,752,1302,1328]" box="[151,752,1302,1328]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,752,1302,1328]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
4. 
<taxonomicName authority="BURMEISTER, 1838" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[181,752,1302,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudophyllinae">PSEUDOPHYLLINAE BURMEISTER, 1838</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1436,1374,1508]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
This subfamily is distributed in most of biogeographical regions, except most of the Palearctic Region and North and South Poles. The subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[514,699,1410,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudophyllinae">Pseudophyllinae</taxonomicName>
encompasses a thousand species distributed in 246 genera and 19 tribes. Current records point to the occurrence of 148 species of 62 genera within 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1151,1446,1472]" name="Brazil" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Here we present records for three tribes of this subfamily, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[525,665,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cocconotini">Cocconotini</taxonomicName>
, Plemiinini and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1960" box="[846,957,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Teleutiini">Teleutiini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
